7. The apparatus of claim 3, wherein the tapering slide comprises:
a wide upper section having a convex bottom wall, a first side wall that is substantially straight and a second side wall that tapers from an outer point aligned with an outer wall of the lower flume;
a narrowing middle section comprising a downwards angled bottom wall, third side wall aligned with the first side wall and a fourth side wall that tapers to narrow the channel formed by the flume.
